Subject:    discarding timed-out data
From:       <a href="?a=95837693200023&r=1&w=2">Mark Crispin &lt;MRC () SIMTEL20 ! ARPA&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198712">1987-12-09 12:36:00</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927085&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927085&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Say, one way to avoid the problem would be to have a separate cell in
the database stating when the last successful contact to that IP address
was.  Then, even if the record was timed-out it would not discard it as
long as that "last successful contact" cell remains reasonably current.

Of course, this means hairing up the data structure to have all sorts of
back-pointers so the TCP layer can find the records...
